00:00:00.630 --> 00:00:02.644
If you've been following
our iOS news lately,

00:00:02.644 --> 00:00:04.810
you've probably heard that
we're now using CocoaPods

00:00:04.810 --> 00:00:07.590
as our primary way of
delivering our libraries to iOS

00:00:07.590 --> 00:00:08.470
developers.

00:00:08.470 --> 00:00:09.307
Hooray!

00:00:09.307 --> 00:00:11.640
But you might have also noticed
that there are sometimes

00:00:11.640 --> 00:00:13.370
a bunch of different
CocoaPods that all

00:00:13.370 --> 00:00:14.950
refer to the same library.

00:00:14.950 --> 00:00:16.390
For example, for
Google Analytics,

00:00:16.390 --> 00:00:19.980
there's Google Analytics
iOS-SKD, GoogleAnalytics,

00:00:19.980 --> 00:00:21.999
and Google/Analytics.

00:00:21.999 --> 00:00:22.790
So what's the deal?

00:00:22.790 --> 00:00:25.836
Are these any different and, if
so, which one should you use?

00:00:25.836 --> 00:00:27.460
Find out the answers
to these questions

00:00:27.460 --> 00:00:29.260
and many more of
life's mysteries

00:00:29.260 --> 00:00:31.998
on this episode of Route 85.

00:00:31.998 --> 00:00:34.866
